A simple program to randomly generate words based on 3-order markov models.


--How to use--

For information about command line options, see ./words.pl --help



--Examples--

prints a list of all datasets: 
  ./words -l

one word from the eng-1M dataset: 
  ./words

twenty words from the eng-1M dataset: 
  ./words 20

one word from the finnish dataset: 
  ./words --finnish

fifteen words from the eng-gb dataset 
  ./words --eng-gb 15

fourteen words from a dataset interpolated from german-medical,
norwegian, finnish, and eng-all datasets: 
  ./words --german-medical --norwegian --finnish --eng-all 14

